<taxonomicName box="[151,371,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalpella" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,371,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Maiestas scalpella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,472,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,472,151,210]" box="[151,385,186,210]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,243,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURE 25. M" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,828,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[188,1398,804,1906]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. M. scalpella sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: style, dorsal view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D &amp; E: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206140/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,186,210]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
; Plate III: F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,258,751]" box="[151,402,258,282]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Length. Male: 3.0mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,258,751]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ochraceous. Vertex with small apical spots on anterior margin brownish (Plate III: F); face stramineous, frontoclypeus with fuscous arcs. Leg marked with dark brown. Forewing with central anteapical cell with basal dark brown spot.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,258,751]" box="[197,895,402,426]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Forewing submacropterous, inner anteapical cell open basally.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,258,751]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,376,438,463]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate long, subtriangular, lateral margin weakly incurved, apex acute (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1402,438,462]" captionStart="FIGURE 25. M" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,828,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[188,1398,804,1906]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. M. scalpella sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: style, dorsal view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D &amp; E: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206140/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[1372,1402,438,462]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
C); style preapical lobe short, apophysis digitate, slightly laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[955,1039,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 25. M" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,828,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[188,1398,804,1906]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. M. scalpella sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: style, dorsal view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D &amp; E: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206140/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[1008,1039,474,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
B); connective slightly shorter than aedeagus, aedeagal shaft very narrow, relatively straight subbasally to apex in lateral view, apex with ventral margin serrate (
<figureCitation box="[283,369,546,570]" captionStart="FIGURE 25. M" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,828,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[188,1398,804,1906]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. M. scalpella sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: style, dorsal view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D &amp; E: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206140/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Figs 
<number box="[340,369,546,570]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
D, 
<number box="[402,432,546,570]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="25.0">25</number>
E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
